# Acme Web API

## Overview

A RESTful API for the Acme e-commerce platform. Handles user management, product catalog, order processing, and payment integration. Built with TypeScript on Node.js with PostgreSQL for persistence.

## Technology Stack

- **Language**: TypeScript 5.7
- **Runtime**: Node.js 22 LTS
- **Framework**: Express 5
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 16 with Prisma ORM
- **Cache**: Redis 7 (session store, rate limiting)
- **Testing**: Vitest + Supertest (API integration tests)
- **Linting**: ESLint 9 (flat config) + Prettier
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions

## Project Structure

| Directory | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `src/` | Application source code |
| `src/api/` | Express route handlers, organized by domain |
| `src/api/middleware/` | Auth, validation, rate limiting, error handling middleware |
| `src/services/` | Business logic layer (called by route handlers) |
| `src/db/` | Prisma schema, migrations, and seed data |
| `src/db/repositories/` | Database access layer (Prisma queries) |
| `src/lib/` | Shared utilities: logging, config, error types |
| `src/jobs/` | Background job processors (order fulfillment, email) |
| `src/types/` | Shared TypeScript type definitions |
| `tests/` | Integration and E2E tests |
| `tests/fixtures/` | Test data factories and fixtures |
| `scripts/` | Development and deployment utilities |
| `docs/` | API documentation (OpenAPI specs) |

## Development Workflow

- Plan features with `/plan` before implementing
- Break plans into tasks with `/tasks`
- Implement with `/implement` for structured execution
- Review with `/review` before committing
- Generate tests with `/test` for uncovered code
- Create PRs with `/pr`

## Build Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `npm run build` | Compile TypeScript to `dist/` |
| `npm run dev` | Start dev server with hot reload (tsx watch) |
| `npm run start` | Start production server |
| `npm test` | Run Vitest test suite |
| `npm run test:watch` | Run tests in watch mode |
| `npm run lint` | Run ESLint |
| `npm run lint:fix` | Auto-fix linting issues |
| `npm run db:migrate` | Run Prisma migrations |
| `npm run db:seed` | Seed development database |
| `npm run db:studio` | Open Prisma Studio |

## Test Commands

```bash
# Run all tests
npm test

# Run specific test file
npx vitest src/api/auth/auth.test.ts

# Run tests matching pattern
npx vitest --grep "should return 401"

# Run with coverage
npx vitest --coverage
```

## Conventions

### Naming
- **Files**: kebab-case (`user-service.ts`, `auth-middleware.ts`)
- **Variables/functions**: camelCase (`getUserById`, `isAuthenticated`)
- **Types/interfaces**: PascalCase (`UserResponse`, `CreateOrderInput`)
- **Database tables**: snake_case plural (`user_accounts`, `order_items`)
- **Environment variables**: SCREAMING_SNAKE (`DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`)

### Error Handling
- Business errors extend `AppError` (includes status code and error code)
- Catch at the API boundary in the error middleware -- services throw, handlers don't catch
- Never swallow errors silently -- always log or re-throw
- Use typed error codes (`USER_NOT_FOUND`, `INSUFFICIENT_STOCK`) not just HTTP status

### API Patterns
- RESTful resource naming: `/api/v1/users`, `/api/v1/orders/{id}/items`
- Request validation with Zod schemas (defined alongside route handlers)
- Pagination: cursor-based for lists, `?cursor=xxx&limit=20`
- Error responses follow RFC 7807 (Problem Details for HTTP APIs)
- All responses wrapped in `{ data, meta }` for lists or `{ data }` for singles

### Testing
- Co-located unit tests: `user-service.test.ts` next to `user-service.ts`
- Integration tests in `tests/`: test full API request/response cycles
- Test factories in `tests/fixtures/` for consistent test data
- Mock external services (payment gateway, email), never mock the database
- Each test describes behavior: `should return 404 when user not found`

### Git
- Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`, `chore:`
- Branch naming: `feat/short-description`, `fix/issue-description`
- PRs reference plan numbers when applicable

## Agents

Available agents in `.claude/agents/`:

| Agent | Role |
|-------|------|
| `typescript-expert` | Senior TS architect for complex type issues and refactoring |
| `api-architect` | Senior API architect for endpoint design and REST conventions |
| `data-engineer` | Senior database engineer for schema design and query optimization |
| `qa-engineer` | Senior QA engineer for test strategy and coverage analysis |

Use the built-in `/agents` command to create and manage sub-agents. See https://code.claude.com/docs/en/sub-agents for the official format.
